#. <section class="sutta" id="sn45.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn45.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 45"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 45"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Avijjāvagga"
msgstr "1. Ignorance"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Jāṇussoṇibrāhmaṇasutta → brāhmaṇasuttaṃ (bj) | brāhmaṇo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn45.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Jāṇussoṇibrāhmaṇasutta"
msgstr "4. Regarding the Brahmin Jāṇussoṇi"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn45.4:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

#. VAR: vaḷavābhirathena → vaḷabhīrathena (bj)
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho āyasmā ānando jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena "
"sāvatthiyā niyyāyantaṃ."
msgstr ""
"He saw the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi driving out of Sāvatthī in a splendid all-white "
"chariot drawn by mares."

msgctxt "sn45.4:1.4"
msgid ""
"Setā sudaṃ assā yuttā honti setālaṅkārā, seto ratho, setaparivāro, setā "
"rasmiyo, setā patodalaṭṭhi, setaṃ chattaṃ, setaṃ uṇhīsaṃ, setāni vatthāni, "
"setā upāhanā, setāya sudaṃ vālabījaniyā bījīyati."
msgstr ""
"The yoked horses were pure white, as were the ornaments, chariot, "
"upholstery, reins, goad, and canopy. And his turban, robes, sandals were "
"white, as was the chowry fanning him."

msgctxt "sn45.4:1.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jano disvā evamāha:"
msgstr "When people saw it they exclaimed:"

# I keep the overly literal Brahma here to retain consistency with the similar usage at AN 3.63. I found that only by keeping the literal form was the sense retained. But I might change my mind!
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.6"
msgid "“brahmaṃ vata, bho, yānaṃ."
msgstr "“Wow! That’s a Brahmā vehicle!"

msgctxt "sn45.4:1.7"
msgid "Brahmayānarūpaṃ vata, bho”ti."
msgstr "It’s a vehicle fit for Brahmā!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Ānanda wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return "
"from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and "
"told him what had happened, adding:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.2"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena "
"sāvatthiyā niyyāyantaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.3"
msgid ""
"Setā sudaṃ assā yuttā honti setālaṅkārā, seto ratho, setaparivāro, setā "
"rasmiyo, setā patodalaṭṭhi, setaṃ chattaṃ, setaṃ uṇhīsaṃ, setāni vatthāni, "
"setā upāhanā, setāya sudaṃ vālabījaniyā bījīyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jano disvā evamāha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.5"
msgid "‘brahmaṃ vata, bho, yānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.6"
msgid "Brahmayānarūpaṃ vata, bho’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.7"
msgid "Sakkā nu kho, bhante, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmayānaṃ paññāpetun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, can you point out a Brahmā vehicle in this teaching and training?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:4.1"
msgid "“Sakkā, ānandā”ti bhagavā avoca:"
msgstr "“I can, Ānanda,” said the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn45.4:4.2"
msgid ""
"“imasseva kho etaṃ, ānanda, ariyassa aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ:"
msgstr "“These are all terms for the noble eightfold path:"

msgctxt "sn45.4:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘brahmayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘dhammayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘anuttaro saṅgāmavijayo’ itipīti."
msgstr ""
"‘vehicle of Brahmā’, or else ‘vehicle of truth’, or else ‘supreme victory in "
"battle’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:5.1"
msgid ""
"Sammādiṭṭhi, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, "
"dosavinayapariyosānā hoti, mohavinayapariyosānā hoti."
msgstr ""
"When right view is developed and cultivated it culminates with the removal "
"of greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.2"
msgid ""
"Sammāsaṅkappo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, "
"dosavinayapariyosāno hoti, mohavinayapariyosāno hoti."
msgstr "When right thought …"

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.3"
msgid ""
"Sammāvācā, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosa … pe … "
"mohavinayapariyosānā hoti."
msgstr "right speech …"

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.4"
msgid ""
"Sammākammanto, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … "
"pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti."
msgstr "right action …"

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.5"
msgid ""
"Sammāājīvo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe …"
" mohavinayapariyosāno hoti."
msgstr "right livelihood …"

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.6"
msgid ""
"Sammāvāyāmo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe "
"… mohavinayapariyosāno hoti."
msgstr "right effort …"

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.7"
msgid ""
"Sammāsati, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosa … pe … "
"mohavinayapariyosānā hoti."
msgstr "right mindfulness …"

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.8"
msgid ""
"Sammāsamādhi, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … "
"pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti."
msgstr ""
"right immersion is developed and cultivated it culminates with the removal "
"of greed, hate, and delusion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:6.1"
msgid ""
"Iminā kho etaṃ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā imassevetaṃ ariyassa "
"aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"This is a way to understand how these are all terms for the noble eightfold "
"path:"

msgctxt "sn45.4:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘brahmayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘dhammayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘anuttaro saṅgāmavijayo’ itipī”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘vehicle of Brahmā’, or else ‘vehicle of truth’, or else ‘supreme victory in "
"battle’.”"

msgctxt "sn45.4:6.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:7.1"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.1"
msgid "“Yassa saddhā ca paññā ca,"
msgstr "“Its qualities of faith and wisdom"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sadā dhuraṃ → saddhā dhuraṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.2"
msgid "Dhammā yuttā sadā dhuraṃ;"
msgstr "are always yoked to the shaft."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.3"
msgid "Hirī īsā mano yottaṃ,"
msgstr "Conscience is its pole, mind its strap,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.4"
msgid "Sati ārakkhasārathi."
msgstr "and mindfulness its careful driver."

# BB has “adornment” here, but parikkhara is always, so far as I know, used in the sense of something essential, as indeed is sila.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.1"
msgid "Ratho sīlaparikkhāro,"
msgstr "The chariot’s equipped with ethics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.2"
msgid "jhānakkho cakkavīriyo;"
msgstr "its axle is absorption, and energy its wheel."

# The Chinese parallel at SA 769 is exact and helpful: 捨三昧為轅. see https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/dhurasamadhi-in-sn-45-4/4157/2
#. <br>
#. VAR: Upekkhā → upekhā (bj)
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.3"
msgid "Upekkhā dhurasamādhi,"
msgstr "Equanimity and immersion are the carriage-shaft,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.4"
msgid "anicchā parivāraṇaṃ."
msgstr "and it’s upholstered with desirelessness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
#. VAR: Abyāpādo → avyāpādo (bj)
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.1"
msgid "Abyāpādo avihiṃsā,"
msgstr "Love, kindness, and seclusion"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.2"
msgid "viveko yassa āvudhaṃ;"
msgstr "are its weapons,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: cammasannāho → vammasannāho (bj) | dhammasannāho (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.3"
msgid "Titikkhā cammasannāho,"
msgstr "patience its shield and armor,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.4"
msgid "yogakkhemāya vattati."
msgstr "as it rolls on to sanctuary."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.1"
msgid "Etadattani sambhūtaṃ,"
msgstr "This supreme Brahmā vehicle"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.2"
msgid "brahmayānaṃ anuttaraṃ;"
msgstr "arises in oneself."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.3"
msgid "Niyyanti dhīrā lokamhā,"
msgstr "The wise leave the world in it,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.4"
msgid "aññadatthu jayaṃ jayan”ti."
msgstr "sure of winning the victory.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
